{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "1ce91ecb-da8a-4552-af9c-bf7a568473de",
		"name": "Availity Mock Eligibility Tests v3",
		"description": "Test collection for Availity eligibility mock scenarios. Uses the 'BF API Local' environment.\n\n## Prerequisites\n- BF.API running locally in Development mode\n- `AvailityMock:UseMock` set to `true` in appsettings.Development.json\n- Valid Auth0 token in `bearerToken` variable\n\n## Environment Variables Used\n- `baseUrl`: API base URL\n- `tenantId`: Test tenant ID\n- `practiceId`: Test practice ID  \n- `patientId`: Valid patient ID (pat_001)\n- `encounterId`: Valid encounter ID (enc_001)\n- `coverageEnrollmentId`: Valid coverage enrollment ID (cov_001_vision)\n- `bearerToken`: Auth0 bearer token\n\n## Mock Scenarios\nEach request uses the `X-Api-Mock-Scenario-ID` header to control mock behavior.\n\n## ForceRefresh Testing\nScenarios 6.x test the ForceRefresh caching behavior:\n- forceRefresh=false: Returns cached result if < 24 hours old\n- forceRefresh=true: Always calls Availity API",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "3424459"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Selective Polling Tests",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "7.1 Setup - Initiate Check #1 (InProgress)",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Verify response status",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200 OK\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Verify mock was used",
									"pm.test(\"Mock response confirmed\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get(\"X-Api-Mock-Response\")).to.eql(\"true\");",
									"});",
									"",
									"var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"",
									"// Save eligibility check ID for selective polling",
									"if (jsonData.eligibilityCheckId) {",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"selectivePollCheckId1\", jsonData.eligibilityCheckId);",
									"    console.log(\"Saved selectivePollCheckId1: \" + jsonData.eligibilityCheckId);",
									"}",
									"",
									"// Verify status is InProgress",
									"pm.test(\"Status is InProgress\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.eql(\"InProgress\");",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Verify nextPollAfterUtc is set",
									"pm.test(\"Next poll time is provided\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.nextPollAfterUtc).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"});",
									"",
									"console.log(\"Check #1 initiated. Now run 7.2 to create Check #2.\");"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{bearerToken}}"
							},
							{
								"key": "X-Api-Mock-Scenario-ID",
								"value": "Coverages-Polling-Success-i",
								"description": "Mock scenario for polling flow"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"coverageEnrollmentId\": \"{{coverageEnrollmentId}}\",\n  \"serviceTypeCodes\": [\"30\"],\n  \"forceRefresh\": true\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/practices/{{practiceId}}/patients/{{patientId}}/encounters/{{encounterId}}/eligibility-checks/run",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"practices",
								"{{practiceId}}",
								"patients",
								"{{patientId}}",
								"encounters",
								"{{encounterId}}",
								"eligibility-checks",
								"run"
							]
						},
						"description": "**Step 1: Create First InProgress Check**\n\nInitiates an eligibility check that requires polling.\nSaves the check ID to `selectivePollCheckId1`.\n\n**Expected:**\n- Status: InProgress\n- nextPollAfterUtc provided"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "7.2 Setup - Initiate Check #2 (InProgress)",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Verify response status",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200 OK\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"",
									"// Save eligibility check ID for selective polling",
									"if (jsonData.eligibilityCheckId) {",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"selectivePollCheckId2\", jsonData.eligibilityCheckId);",
									"    console.log(\"Saved selectivePollCheckId2: \" + jsonData.eligibilityCheckId);",
									"}",
									"",
									"// Verify status is InProgress",
									"pm.test(\"Status is InProgress\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.eql(\"InProgress\");",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Build comma-separated list of check IDs",
									"var checkId1 = pm.environment.get(\"selectivePollCheckId1\");",
									"var checkId2 = jsonData.eligibilityCheckId;",
									"var checksReadyToPoll = checkId1 + \",\" + checkId2;",
									"pm.environment.set(\"checksReadyToPoll\", checksReadyToPoll);",
									"",
									"console.log(\"Check #2 initiated.\");",
									"console.log(\"checksReadyToPoll: \" + checksReadyToPoll);",
									"console.log(\"\");",
									"console.log(\"Now run 7.3 to list checks (no polling).\");"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{bearerToken}}"
							},
							{
								"key": "X-Api-Mock-Scenario-ID",
								"value": "Coverages-Polling-Success-i",
								"description": "Mock scenario for polling flow"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"coverageEnrollmentId\": \"{{coverageEnrollmentId}}\",\n  \"serviceTypeCodes\": [\"35\"],\n  \"forceRefresh\": true\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/practices/{{practiceId}}/patients/{{patientId}}/encounters/{{encounterId}}/eligibility-checks/run",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"practices",
								"{{practiceId}}",
								"patients",
								"{{patientId}}",
								"encounters",
								"{{encounterId}}",
								"eligibility-checks",
								"run"
							]
						},
						"description": "**Step 2: Create Second InProgress Check**\n\nInitiates a second eligibility check.\nBuilds the `checksReadyToPoll` comma-separated list.\n\n**Expected:**\n- Status: InProgress\n- checksReadyToPoll contains both check IDs"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "7.3 List Checks (No Polling)",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Verify response status",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200 OK\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"",
									"// Verify checks array returned",
									"pm.test(\"Checks array returned\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.be.an('array');",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.length).to.be.at.least(2);",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Count checks by status",
									"var inProgressCount = jsonData.filter(c => c.status === 'InProgress').length;",
									"var completeCount = jsonData.filter(c => c.status === 'Complete').length;",
									"",
									"console.log(\"=== ELIGIBILITY CHECKS LIST (NO POLLING) ===\");",
									"console.log(\"Total checks: \" + jsonData.length);",
									"console.log(\"InProgress: \" + inProgressCount);",
									"console.log(\"Complete: \" + completeCount);",
									"console.log(\"\");",
									"",
									"// Verify our test checks are InProgress",
									"var checkId1 = pm.environment.get(\"selectivePollCheckId1\");",
									"var checkId2 = pm.environment.get(\"selectivePollCheckId2\");",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Both test checks are InProgress\", function () {",
									"    var check1 = jsonData.find(c => c.eligibilityCheckId === checkId1);",
									"    var check2 = jsonData.find(c => c.eligibilityCheckId === checkId2);",
									"    pm.expect(check1).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"    pm.expect(check2).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"    pm.expect(check1.status).to.eql(\"InProgress\");",
									"    pm.expect(check2.status).to.eql(\"InProgress\");",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Show poll counts (should be 0 since no polling happened)",
									"jsonData.forEach(function(check) {",
									"    if (check.eligibilityCheckId === checkId1 || check.eligibilityCheckId === checkId2) {",
									"        console.log(check.eligibilityCheckId + \": pollCount=\" + check.pollCount);",
									"    }",
									"});",
									"",
									"console.log(\"\");",
									"console.log(\"Now run 7.4 to selectively poll both checks.\");"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{bearerToken}}"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/practices/{{practiceId}}/patients/{{patientId}}/encounters/{{encounterId}}/eligibility-checks",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"practices",
								"{{practiceId}}",
								"patients",
								"{{patientId}}",
								"encounters",
								"{{encounterId}}",
								"eligibility-checks"
							]
						},
						"description": "**Step 3: List All Checks (No Polling)**\n\n**Endpoint:** GET /eligibility-checks\n\n**NO `pollCheckIds` parameter** = No Availity calls made.\n\nThis is the baseline - shows current state without triggering any polls.\n\n**RU Cost:** ~1 RU (read only)"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "7.4 Selective Poll - Both Checks",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Verify response status",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200 OK\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Verify mock was used (Availity was called for polling)",
									"pm.test(\"Mock response confirmed (polling occurred)\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get(\"X-Api-Mock-Response\")).to.eql(\"true\");",
									"});",
									"",
									"var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"var checkId1 = pm.environment.get(\"selectivePollCheckId1\");",
									"var checkId2 = pm.environment.get(\"selectivePollCheckId2\");",
									"",
									"// Verify checks array returned",
									"pm.test(\"Checks array returned\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.be.an('array');",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.length).to.be.at.least(2);",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Verify poll counts incremented",
									"pm.test(\"Poll counts incremented for requested checks\", function () {",
									"    var check1 = jsonData.find(c => c.eligibilityCheckId === checkId1);",
									"    var check2 = jsonData.find(c => c.eligibilityCheckId === checkId2);",
									"    pm.expect(check1.pollCount).to.be.at.least(1);",
									"    pm.expect(check2.pollCount).to.be.at.least(1);",
									"});",
									"",
									"console.log(\"=== SELECTIVE POLLING RESULT ===\");",
									"console.log(\"Requested to poll: 2 checks\");",
									"console.log(\"\");",
									"",
									"jsonData.forEach(function(check) {",
									"    if (check.eligibilityCheckId === checkId1 || check.eligibilityCheckId === checkId2) {",
									"        console.log(check.eligibilityCheckId + \":\");",
									"        console.log(\"  Status: \" + check.status);",
									"        console.log(\"  Poll Count: \" + check.pollCount);",
									"        console.log(\"  Next Poll After: \" + (check.nextPollAfterUtc || 'N/A'));",
									"    }",
									"});",
									"",
									"console.log(\"\");",
									"console.log(\"RU Cost Estimate:\");",
									"console.log(\"  Selective: 1 RU (read) + 2 × 1.5 RU (polls) = 4 RU\");",
									"console.log(\"  Traditional: 2 × 2.5 RU (individual GETs) = 5 RU\");",
									"console.log(\"  Savings: 1 RU (20% reduction)\");"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{bearerToken}}"
							},
							{
								"key": "X-Api-Mock-Scenario-ID",
								"value": "Coverages-Polling-Success-i",
								"description": "Must match scenario used in initiate"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/practices/{{practiceId}}/patients/{{patientId}}/encounters/{{encounterId}}/eligibility-checks?pollCheckIds={{checksReadyToPoll}}",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"practices",
								"{{practiceId}}",
								"patients",
								"{{patientId}}",
								"encounters",
								"{{encounterId}}",
								"eligibility-checks"
							],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "pollCheckIds",
									"value": "{{checksReadyToPoll}}",
									"description": "Comma-separated check IDs to poll"
								}
							]
						},
						"description": "**Step 4: Selective Poll**\n\n**Endpoint:** GET /eligibility-checks?pollCheckIds={id1},{id2}\n\n**WITH `pollCheckIds` parameter** = Availity called for specified checks only.\n\n**Benefits:**\n- Single API call polls multiple checks\n- Respects nextPollAfterUtc\n- 20-35% RU cost reduction vs individual GETs"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "7.5 Verify Poll Counts Incremented",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Verify response status",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200 OK\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"var checkId1 = pm.environment.get(\"selectivePollCheckId1\");",
									"var checkId2 = pm.environment.get(\"selectivePollCheckId2\");",
									"",
									"// Find our test checks",
									"var check1 = jsonData.find(c => c.eligibilityCheckId === checkId1);",
									"var check2 = jsonData.find(c => c.eligibilityCheckId === checkId2);",
									"",
									"// Verify poll counts are at least 1",
									"pm.test(\"Check #1 poll count >= 1\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(check1.pollCount).to.be.at.least(1);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Check #2 poll count >= 1\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(check2.pollCount).to.be.at.least(1);",
									"});",
									"",
									"console.log(\"=== POLL COUNT VERIFICATION ===\");",
									"console.log(\"Check #1 (\" + checkId1 + \"):\");",
									"console.log(\"  Status: \" + check1.status);",
									"console.log(\"  Poll Count: \" + check1.pollCount);",
									"console.log(\"\");",
									"console.log(\"Check #2 (\" + checkId2 + \"):\");",
									"console.log(\"  Status: \" + check2.status);",
									"console.log(\"  Poll Count: \" + check2.pollCount);",
									"console.log(\"\");",
									"console.log(\"Selective polling verified! Both checks were polled in a single API call.\");"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{bearerToken}}"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/practices/{{practiceId}}/patients/{{patientId}}/encounters/{{encounterId}}/eligibility-checks",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"practices",
								"{{practiceId}}",
								"patients",
								"{{patientId}}",
								"encounters",
								"{{encounterId}}",
								"eligibility-checks"
							]
						},
						"description": "**Step 5: Verify Polling Occurred**\n\n**Endpoint:** GET /eligibility-checks (no pollCheckIds)\n\nConfirms that the selective polling actually polled the requested checks by verifying `pollCount >= 1`."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "7.6 Continue Polling Until Complete",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Verify response status",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200 OK\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"var checkId1 = pm.environment.get(\"selectivePollCheckId1\");",
									"var checkId2 = pm.environment.get(\"selectivePollCheckId2\");",
									"",
									"// Find our test checks",
									"var check1 = jsonData.find(c => c.eligibilityCheckId === checkId1);",
									"var check2 = jsonData.find(c => c.eligibilityCheckId === checkId2);",
									"",
									"console.log(\"=== POLLING STATUS ===\");",
									"console.log(\"Check #1: \" + check1.status + \" (pollCount: \" + check1.pollCount + \")\");",
									"console.log(\"Check #2: \" + check2.status + \" (pollCount: \" + check2.pollCount + \")\");",
									"",
									"// Check if both are complete",
									"var allComplete = check1.status === 'Complete' && check2.status === 'Complete';",
									"",
									"if (allComplete) {",
									"    pm.test(\"Both checks Complete\", function () {",
									"        pm.expect(check1.status).to.eql(\"Complete\");",
									"        pm.expect(check2.status).to.eql(\"Complete\");",
									"    });",
									"    ",
									"    console.log(\"\");",
									"    console.log(\"All checks complete! Selective polling flow finished.\");",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log(\"\");",
									"    console.log(\"Not all complete yet. Run this request again to continue polling.\");",
									"    console.log(\"(Mock requires 3 polls to complete)\");",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{bearerToken}}"
							},
							{
								"key": "X-Api-Mock-Scenario-ID",
								"value": "Coverages-Polling-Success-i",
								"description": "Must match scenario used in initiate"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/practices/{{practiceId}}/patients/{{patientId}}/encounters/{{encounterId}}/eligibility-checks?pollCheckIds={{checksReadyToPoll}}",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"practices",
								"{{practiceId}}",
								"patients",
								"{{patientId}}",
								"encounters",
								"{{encounterId}}",
								"eligibility-checks"
							],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "pollCheckIds",
									"value": "{{checksReadyToPoll}}",
									"description": "Comma-separated check IDs to poll"
								}
							]
						},
						"description": "**Step 6: Continue Polling**\n\nRun this request 2-3 times until both checks are Complete.\n\nThe mock scenario `Coverages-Polling-Success-i` requires 3 polls to complete."
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Tests for the selective polling API optimization using `pollCheckIds` parameter.\n\n**Selective Polling Pattern:**\n1. GET /eligibility-checks (no polling) - Get current state\n2. Client identifies checks where `nextPollAfterUtc <= now`\n3. GET /eligibility-checks?pollCheckIds=id1,id2 - Poll only ready checks\n\n**Benefits:**\n- Single API call polls multiple checks\n- Respects `nextPollAfterUtc` to avoid premature polling\n- 20-35% RU cost reduction\n\n**Run these tests in order:**\n1. 7.1 Setup - Create Check #1 (InProgress)\n2. 7.2 Setup - Create Check #2 (InProgress)\n3. 7.3 List Checks (No Polling) - Verify baseline\n4. 7.4 Selective Poll - Poll both checks\n5. 7.5 Verify Poll Counts Incremented\n6. 7.6 Continue Polling Until Complete"
		},
		{
			"name": "1. Success - Immediate Complete",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"// Verify response status",
							"pm.test(\"Status code is 200 OK\", function () {",
							"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
							"});",
							"",
							"// Verify mock was used",
							"pm.test(\"Mock response confirmed\", function () {",
							"    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get(\"X-Api-Mock-Response\")).to.eql(\"true\");",
							"});",
							"",
							"// Parse response",
							"var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
							"",
							"// Save eligibility check ID for later use",
							"if (jsonData.eligibilityCheckId) {",
							"    pm.environment.set(\"createdEligibilityCheckId\", jsonData.eligibilityCheckId);",
							"    console.log(\"Saved createdEligibilityCheckId: \" + jsonData.eligibilityCheckId);",
							"}",
							"",
							"// Verify status is Complete",
							"pm.test(\"Status is Complete\", function () {",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.eql(\"Complete\");",
							"});",
							"",
							"// Verify raw status code is 4 (Availity Complete)",
							"pm.test(\"Raw status code is 4\", function () {",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData.rawStatusCode).to.eql(\"4\");",
							"});",
							"",
							"// Verify coverage lines exist",
							"pm.test(\"Has coverage lines\", function () {",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData.coverageLines).to.be.an('array');",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData.coverageLines.length).to.be.greaterThan(0);",
							"});",
							"",
							"// Verify plan name is populated",
							"pm.test(\"Plan name is populated\", function () {",
